"'''Nouveau pauvre'''" ("new poor"), refers to a person who had once owned considerable wealth, but has now lost all or most of it. This term is generally used to emphasize that the individual was previously part of a higher socioeconomic rank, and that such wealth that provided the means for the acquisition of goods or luxuries is currently unobtainable. These people may or may not actually be poor, but compared to their previous rank, it seems as if they are.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.recessionwire.com/2009/06/15/definition-of-nouveau-poor/ |title=Recession Lexicon: Nouveau Poor |last=Rich |first=Laura |date=June 15, 2009 |publisher=Recessionwire |accessdate=2009-08-27 |deadurl=bot: unknown |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090829144529/http://www.recessionwire.com/2009/06/15/definition-of-nouveau-poor/ |archivedate=August 29, 2009 |df= }}</ref>

