'''[[Polygamy]]''' is illegal in '''[[Burundi]]''' and the nation does not recognize polygamous marriages under civil law or customary law. A 1993 [[Law|amendment]] to the Code of Person and Family officially abolished polygamy in the country. Even still, the practice is still present in Burundi and has reportedly increased rather than decreased, mainly due to recent conflicts and crises.<ref>[http://genderindex.org/country/burundi Burundi: Family Code]</ref>

